   <head>[Lines Written at Burnham]</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And, as they bow their hoary tops, relate</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">In murmuring sounds the dark decrees of fate;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">While visions, as poetic eyes avow,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Cling to each leaf and swarm on every bough:</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
